		<div class="content">
			<h2 class="lead">We are looking for sharp talent to join our team!</h2>

				<p class="col2span">


				<!--
					At GeoFields,  based primarily on the people we hire.
					We look for people who are self-motivated, passionate, creative team players. We recognize that the right people, offering their ideas and expertise, will enable us to continue our success.
				-->

				GeoFields, Inc., a privately held company founded in 1996, provides the highest quality data management solutions to the oil and gas pipeline industry. With offices in Atlanta, one of the nation's leading high-tech hubs, and Houston, the energy capital of the world, GeoFields is committed to remaining the pipeline industry's leading provider of proven data management solutions. We are actively recruiting people who understand the power of innovation with excellence. This translates into growth opportunities for the right technology professionals, such as GIS Analysts, GIS Software Engineers, Database Developers, Project Managers, Application Support Analysts and Account Managers.</p>




				<hr style="border: 0; color: #ccc; background-color: #eee; height: 1px;">
				<img src="../../pics/crumb-arrow.gif" style="border:0; margin:0 0 0 -8px; padding:11px 0 0 0;"><h3><a href='javascript: toggle8()' id="database-developer">Database Developer</a></h3>
				<div style="padding-left:35px;">
					<div id='divjob8' style='display:none'>
						<p class="col2span">The position of Database Developer is responsible for analyzing, designing, implementing and administering complex relational database queries and applications. The position requires cross-functional abilities in the development and administration, programming and testing, troubleshooting/reengineering, and maintenance of large-scale, complex databases. Excellent knowledge of SQL Server and expertise in designing processes to ensure data integrity is a must. The position requires a highly motivated, enthusiastic professional with a strong work ethic.</p>
						<p>We are currently looking for a professional with a minimum of three years experience in database development with MS SQL Server and/or Oracle. The individual should have training and/or work experience with: relational database theory, design, and implementation, MS SQL Server and Oracle programming, and SQL Server functionality. Must be self-motivated and a team player.</p>
							<h4>Responsibilities:</h4>
								<ul>
									<li>SQL Database programming:</il>
											<ul style="padding-bottom:5px;">
												<li>Build SQL query modules, stored procedures, triggers, views and reports.</li>
												<li>Debug code; ensure integrity of database programs.</li>
												<li>Develop and Modify SQL stored procedures.</li>
												<li>Design and implement workflow processes.</li>
											</ul>
									<li>Perform intermediate DBA tasks:</il>
											<ul style="padding-bottom:5px;">
												<li>Database Security.</li>
												<li>Performance Tuning.</li>
												<li>Backup and recovery.</li>
											</ul>
									<li>Database Design:</il>
											<ul style="padding-bottom:5px;">
												<li>Work with database team to design database to meet business requirements.</li>
												<li>Work in a team environment.</li>
												<li>Work with application developers to write, implement and advise on stored procedures, triggers, etc.</li>
												<li>Prioritize work tasks and proactively communicate status of work items.</li>
											</ul>
									<li>Maintain existing database systems:</il>
											<ul style="padding-bottom:5px;">
												<li>MS Access</li>
												<li>SQL Server</li>
												<li>Oracle</li>
											</ul>
									</li>
								</ul>
							<h4>Requirements</h4>
								<ul>
									<li>Strong SQL Database programmer with SQL Server experience:</li>
											<ul style="padding-bottom:5px;">
												<li>Stored procedures</li>
												<li>Triggers</li>
												<li>Constraints</li>
												<li>Views </li>
												<li>Knowledge of complex SQL queries, methodologies, and design.</li>
												<li>Excellent analytical skills.</li>
											</ul>
									<li>Experience in API design/documentation.</li>
									<li>Ability to multitask and work within tight schedules.</li>
									<li>Excellent verbal, written communication and interpersonal skills.</li>
									<li>Work and thrive in a team environment and mentor others.</li>
									<li>Experience in both SQL Server and Oracle.</li>
								</ul>

							<h4>Additional desirable skills</h4>
								<ul>
									<li>Experience with ESRI ArcGIS, especially ArcSDE, geodatabase design and migration</li>
									<li>Experience working with very large datasets and databases.</li>
									<li>Experience with Data Warehousing.</li>
									<li>ODBC, OLEDB and other middleware experience.</li>
								</ul>
							<h4>Location</h4>
								<p>Atlanta</p>
							<h4>Travel</h4>
								<p>0% - 10% dependent on project needs.</p>
							<h4>Apply</h4>
								<p>Please email your resume and supporting materials to careers (at) geofields.com with the subject line <em>Database Developer</em>. Candidates must have U.S. Citizenship, Permanent Resident Status, or be a Green Card holder to be considered for this position.</p>
					</div>
				</div>



				<hr style="border: 0; color: #ccc; background-color: #eee; height: 1px;">
				<img src="../../pics/crumb-arrow.gif" style="border:0; margin:0 0 0 -8px; padding:11px 0 0 0;"><h3><a href='javascript: toggle()' id="GIS-analyst">GIS Analyst</a></h3>
				<div style="padding-left:35px;">
					<div id='divjob1' style='display:none'>
						<p class="col2span">GeoFields, a recognized leader of managed data solutions for the oil and gas pipeline industry, is expanding and presently has GIS Analyst positions open in our Atlanta office. GeoFields provides advanced data management solutions to the oil and gas pipeline industry. Our solutions and services support asset/facility data management, integrity/risk management, and project data management.</p><p>The successful candidate will have the opportunity to work with a progressive team of analysts, software engineers, and developers to develop and deliver comprehensive solutions for the oil and gas pipeline industry.</p>
							<h4>Desired Skills:</h4>
								<p>A GIS Analyst is responsible for day-to-day project execution and data deliverables. Projects and tasks may include but are not limited to data collection and integration, map production, and advanced spatial analysis. The successful candidate must have one to two years of proven GIS experience. Experience with ArcGIS 9.x, SQL, and MS Access are required; experience with Python scripting and linear referencing are strongly desired.</p>
							<h4>Responsibilities:</h4>
								<ul>
									<li>Client satisfaction</li>
									<li>Technical client meetings and presentations as needed</li>
									<li>Documentation and improvement of production processes</li>
									<li>Technical project tasks, including database design, advanced GIS analysis and modeling</li>
									<li>Responsible for quality control of both data and process of work</li>
									<li>Ability to communicate task status, needs and issues to team members</li>
									<li>Ability to meet given task scheduling and budget requirements</li>
									<li>Assist Development group with data and data manipulation requests</li>
									<li>Operation of all GeoFields software to suit client needs</li>
								</ul>
							<h4>Requirements</h4>
								<ul>
									<li>University degree in Geography or related field and two years experience.</li>
									<li>Proven history of successful project execution</li>
									<li>Ability to perform advanced GIS analysis</li>
									<li>Thorough understanding of the Esri product family, including ArcGIS (plus extensions), ArcSDE, ArcServer, and related products</li>
									<li>Strong SQL skills</li>
									<li>Strong communication skills</li>
									<li>Highly self motivated - driven to &#8220;get the job done&#8221;</li>
									<li>Proven history of &#8220;do it once, do it right&#8221;</li>
								</ul>
							<h4>Location</h4>
								<p>Atlanta</p>
							<h4>Travel</h4>
								<p>0% - 10% dependent on project needs.</p>
							<h4>Apply</h4>
								<p>Please email your resume and supporting materials to careers (at) geofields.com with the subject line <em>GIS Analyst</em>.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				




