				<hr style="border: 0; color: #ccc; background-color: #eee; height: 1px;">
				<img src="../../pics/crumb-arrow.gif" style="border:0; margin:0 0 0 -8px; padding:11px 0 0 0;"><h3><a href='javascript: toggle5()' id="Integrity-Engineer">Pipeline Integrity Engineer</a></h3>
				<div style="padding-left:35px;">
					<div id='divjob5' style='display:none'>
						<p class="col2span">GeoFields, Inc., a leading oil and gas pipeline application development, data management, and consulting firm, is expanding and presently has multiple Pipeline Integrity Engineer positions open at various levels. GeoFields provides advanced data management solutions to the oil and gas pipeline industry. Our solutions and services support asset/facility data management, integrity/risk management, and project data management. GeoFields maintains offices in Atlanta, GA and Houston, TX. Positions are available in both offices, and remotely located candidates will also be considered.</p>
						<p>The successful candidate will have the opportunity to work with a progressive team of analysts, engineers, and software specialists to develop and deliver comprehensive solutions for the oil and gas pipeline industry. Current clients include leading oil and gas pipeline operators in North America, EMEA, and South America.</p>
							<h4>Desired Skills:</h4>
								<p>This person will be responsible for day-to-day project execution and deliverables related to GeoFields integrity and risk consulting activities. Projects and tasks may include but are not limited to consulting, risk model configuration, evaluation of assessment results, audit support, High Consequence Area (HCA) analysis, and related engineering activities. Experience with GIS implementation in support of Pipeline Integrity Management Systems (PIMS) is strongly desired.</p>
							<h4>Requirements</h4>
								<ul>
									<li>Develops and implements standards and procedures to support the Integrity Management Program (IMP).</li>
									<li>Develops written Integrity Management Programs for a variety of oil and gas pipeline operators worldwide</li>
									<li>Identifies preventive and mitigative measures and processes to determine reassessment intervals and methods</li>
									<li>Provides engineering support for pipeline integrity projects including MOP/MAOP calculations, evaluation of defects and repair recommendations.</li>
									<li>Evaluates integrity assessment results to determine need for temporary pressure reductions and/or the need for repairs and associated repair methods.</li>
									<li>Client satisfaction</li>
									<li>Technical client meetings and presentations as needed</li>
									<li>Ability to communicate task status, needs and issues to team members</li>
									<li>Ability to meet given task scheduling and budget requirements</li>
									<li>Stays current with pipeline regulations, industry standards, integrity assessment methods, repair methods and other applicable technologies.</li>
								</ul>
							<h4>Minimum Requirements</h4>
								<ul>
									<li>A minimum of a Bachelor's Degree in Engineering is required; Mechanical, Civil, Chemical, or Metallurgy degree is preferred.</li>
									<li>5 years of transmission integrity experience</li>
									<li>Proven history of successful project execution</li>
									<li>Strong communication skills</li>
								</ul>
							<h4>Requirements</h4>
								<ul>
									<li>Experience with GIS- based Pipeline Data Management, Risk Assessment, and Integrity Management processes using the Esri GIS platform.</li>
									<li>PE license or EIT</li>
									<li>NACE Certification - Corrosion or CP Technologist/Specialist</li>
								</ul>
							<h4>Location</h4>
								<p>Atlanta or Houston</p>
							<h4>Travel</h4>
								<p>25% average dependent on project needs.</p>
							<h4>Apply</h4>
								<p>Please email your resume and supporting materials to careers (at) geofields.com with the subject line <em>Pipeline Integrity Engineer</em>.</p>
					</div>
				</div>


