				<hr style="border: 0; color: #ccc; background-color: #eee; height: 1px;">
				<img src="../../pics/crumb-arrow.gif" style="border:0; margin:0 0 0 -8px; padding:11px 0 0 0;"><h3><a href='javascript: toggle7()' id="product-manager">Product Manager</a></h3>
				<div style="padding-left:35px;">
				<div id='divjob7' style='display:none'>
					<p>GeoFields is looking for a high-energy, self-directed and customer-focused product manager for our software platform. This person will provide technical leadership requiring specialized expertise, creativity, initiative and sound business &#38; technical judgment. They will produce product strategies, requirements and roadmaps, coordinate relationships with development groups, and develop/manage appropriate external relationships to maximize product excellence.</p>
					<p>Our ideal candidate is experienced in enterprise software product management, with Agile development knowledge with Esri ArcGIS and pipeline industry knowledge a plus. He or she must be detailed-driven, have great organization and time-management skills, enjoy travelling, communicating with customers, effectively communicating business requirements to technical internal resources, and effectively communicating the market needs through the software to sales and marketing.</p>

					<h4>Responsibilities:</h4>
						<ul>
							<li>Manage entire product line life cycle of both desktop and web applications from strategic planning to tactical activities</li>
							<li>Specify market requirements for current and future products by conducting market research supported by on-going visits to customers and non-customers</li>
							<li>Responsible for product strategy and vision and creating product forecasts and roadmaps</li>
							<li>Translate market requirements into prioritized product functionality requirements and specifications.</li>
							<li>Drive a solution set across development teams (primarily Development/Engineering, Quality Assurance, Database Administrators and UI Experts) to specify functional enhancements to product, release planning and sprint reviews, acceptance tests and benchmarking. Manages progress and coordinates development of product enhancements.</li>
							<li>Lead demonstrations and presentations of products to upper management, Marketing and Sales.</li>
							<li>Provide support for sales and marketing with product placement, releases, presentations, demonstrations to current and potential clients and other related activities</li>
							<li>Assist training team with training materials, setup and training content</li>
							<li>Assist Sales at industry tradeshows, present and fully participate at company user conference and demonstrate products and train on-site when needed</li>
						</ul>
					<h4>Desired Skills &#38; Experience:</h4>
						<ul>
							<li>5+ years experience in software Product Management</li>
							<li>Demonstrated success in defining and launching excellent products</li>
							<li>Bachelor or advanced degree in geography, GIS, Computer Science, Marketing or Engineering</li>
							<li>Ample experience with software Agile development methodologies</li>
							<li>Technical background with GIS (ArcGIS and ArcGIS Server) a plus</li>
							<li>Working knowledge of SQL and Oracle Databases</li>
							<li>Exceptional  written and verbal communication and presentation skills</li>
							<li>Excellent analytical, organizational, teamwork and leadership skills</li>
							<li>Proven ability to influence cross-functional teams without formal authority</li>
							<li>US Citizenship preferred</li>
						</ul>
					<h4>Location:</h4>
						<p>Headquarters in Atlanta, GA</p>
					<h4>Travel requirement:</h4>
						<p>Travel to existing and prospective client sites as required. 10-25%</p>
					<p>Interested applicants should send a resume to careers (at) geofields.com with the subject line <em>Product Manager</em>.</p>
				</div>
				</div>









				<hr style="border: 0; color: #ccc; background-color: #eee; height: 1px;">
				<img src="../../pics/crumb-arrow.gif" style="border:0; margin:0 0 0 -8px; padding:11px 0 0 0;"><h3><a href='javascript: toggle9()' id="ui-dev">User Interface Developer</a></h3>
				<div style="padding-left:35px;">
				<div id='divjob9' style='display:none'>
					<p>GeoFields is seeking talented user interface developer. The successful candidate should have experience with C#. Knowledge of MVVM and MVC patterns and SilverLight experience necessary desirable but not necessary. This position requires an individual with strong communication and collaboration skills as well as excellent coding habits including code documentation, and the ability to follow specifications and coding standards.</p>

					<h4>General Description:</h4>
						<ul>
							<li>This role will design user interfaces for new products and integrate into existing back end code, based upon functional requirements and technical specifications, follow the established software development methodology, review the work of peers to ensure consistency and quality, provide status updates of work progress and keep up to date with emerging Microsoft technologies.</li>
						</ul>
					<h4>Desired Skills &#38; Experience:</h4>
						<ul>
							<li>BS in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field</li>
							<li>Experience in coding both Web and Windows Form based applications using Microsoft technologies</li>
							<li>At least 3 years of experience with C#</li>
							<li>Experience in writing software utilizing XML</li>
							<li>Strong problem-solving, analytical, and conceptual skills and a strong working knowledge of object-oriented concepts and software patterns. Prefer candidates that are self-motivated and able to participate in the organization and execution of large-scale projects.</li>
							<li>Knowledge and experience with Telerik controls is a plus</li>
							<li>Knowledge and experience with SilverLight is a plus</li>
						</ul>
					<h4>Location:</h4>
						<p>Headquarters in Atlanta, GA</p>
					<p>Interested applicants should send a resume to careers (at) geofields.com with the subject line <em>UI Developer</em>.</p>
				</div>
				</div>




